# Kaka, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Kaka (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Akhtynsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 1,667 as of 2012. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Kaka is located 11&nbsp;km west of Akhty (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kaluk is the nearest rural locality.
